In [11]:
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
def lemmatize(data):
    text = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in data]
    return data


Data['full_text'] = Data['full_text'].apply(lambda x: lemmatize(x))
In [12]:
#ASSIGNING THE POLARITY

def polarity(text):
    return TextBlob(text).polarity
Data['polarity'] = Data['full_text'].apply(polarity)
def sentiment(label):
    if label<0:
        return "Negetive"
    elif label == 0:
        return "Neutral"
    elif label>0:
        return "Positive"
Data['Sentiment'] = Data['polarity'].apply(sentiment)

# Weightage of the words in the tweets
stop_words = [frozenset(stop_words)]
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_df = 0.95, min_df = 2, stop_words = stop_words)
x = vectorizer.fit_transform(negetive_reviwes)
# Lda model
num_topics = 6
lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components = num_topics, random_state=1)
lda.fit(x)

In [75]:
num_top_words = 7
feature_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()
topics=[]
In [76]:
# Extracting the topics from LDA model
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):
    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[:-num_top_words - 1:-1]
    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]
    topics.append(top_words)

for i, topic in enumerate(topics):
    print(f"Topic {i+1}: {',' .join(topic)}")

WordCloud¶

In [78]:
res = [' '.join(ele) for ele in topics]
text = ' '.join([word for word in res])
plt.figure(figsize=(20,15), facecolor='None')
wordcloud= WordCloud(max_words=500, width=1600, height=800).generate(text)
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis("off")
plt.title('Most frequent words in Negetive Tweets (visa)', fontsize=19)
plt.show()

Observation for negative tweets:

1) Visa Service Issues:

• Any technical glitches can cause delay. lack of visa facilities, and administrative errors are causing passenger dissatisfaction and delays at the airport. Instances of flight delays, lack of information, and mismanagement of flight schedules are causing inconvenience for travellers.

3) Poor Management services:

• By poor visa check and management service the immigration process can be slowed down and this can happen when there is lack of coordination at the airport.

# Extracting the topics from LDA model
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):

for i, topic in enumerate(topics):

Observation for positive tweets:

1) Improved visa Process and easy access:

• The security process at Bangalore Airport was smooth and hassle-free which allowed passengers to complete the procedure quickly and without any unnecessary delays. • The bangalore airport had a very easy to access environment which helps in the immigration sector. .

2) Convenient location and accessibility: • The convenient location of the Red Key Airport Hotel on Kempegowda International Airport Road was mentioned which offered budget-friendly accommodation and welcoming hospitality for guests.

3) Enhanced Technologies and developments:

• There are continuous efforts to develop and help the immigrats and the service is done in the efficient way.The airport has used modern technology which includes the DigiYatra system, to streamline and simplify the security process.
